New StormWizard Demos
=====================

Demo 1 - shows Manipulations on some wizard.library Gadgets
Demo 2 - complete app converting a character to its ASCII-code
Demo 3 - demonstrates working with EasyRequests and ASL file requesters
Demo 4 - demonstrates data exchange between windows
Demo 5 - demonstrates enabling/disabling gadgets

All sources are heavily commented for better understanding.

Hints:
These Demos were written while attempting to understand how StormWizard works and how to write apps using this GUI.
Differently to those demos included in the StormWizard archive, my new demos are aiming at beeing compilable either
using StormC/StormGCC/SAS-C/GCC or VBCC. Parts of their code ara based on the Work of Bernd Rösch (maintainer of StormWizard),
beeing adapted to compile under nearly every available decent Amiga C compiler.

The Demos have been developed under WinUAE/Workbench 3.9/AfA and testet on a "real" Amiga A1200HD. They are published "as is" with
the aim of beeing usefull for studies on wizard.library. Pleas send bug reports, ideas, proposals and so on to amiga68k@gmx.de

Michael Bergmann, October 2012
